## File Naming Conventions

### Phase Documentation
- Format: `PHASE{N}_{TITLE}.md`
- Examples:
  - `PHASE2_ACCESSIBILITY_COMPLETE.md` - Phase completion report
  - `PHASE2_SESSION_COMPLETE.md` - Session summary
  - `PHASE3_PERFORMANCE_PLAN.md` - Phase plan
  - `STATUS_PHASES_1-3_COMPLETE.md` - Status overview

### Guide Documentation
- Format: `{TOPIC}_GUIDE.md`
- Examples:
  - `ACCESSIBILITY_GUIDE.md`
  - `PERFORMANCE_GUIDE.md`
  - `TESTING_GUIDE.md`

### API Documentation
- Format: `{COMPONENT_TYPE}_API.md`
- Examples:
  - `UTILITIES_API.md`
  - `HOOKS_API.md`
  - `COMPONENTS_API.md`

## Documentation Rules

### 1. Every Phase Must Have:
```
- Phase plan document
- Implementation summary
- Completion report
- Session notes
- Quick start guide
```

### 2. Document Structure Template:

```markdown
# {TITLE}

**Date:** {DATE}
**Phase:** {N}/{TOTAL}
**Status:** {STATUS}

## Overview
- Brief description
- Key achievements
- Metrics

## Deliverables
- List of created files
- Lines of code
- Tests/coverage

## Documentation
- Links to related docs
- Quick start
- Next steps

## Files
- Created files list
- Modified files list
```

### 3. Update Checklist per Phase:
```
Phase Start:
- [ ] Create PHASE{N}_*.md files in docs/phases/
- [ ] Update TRAVEL_DETAILS_TODO.md for phase status
- [ ] Create guide in docs/guides/

Phase Completion:
- [ ] Write completion report
- [ ] Move to docs/phases/
- [ ] Update status document
- [ ] Create session summary
- [ ] Link to guides

Quality Check:
- [ ] All links working
- [ ] Code examples correct
- [ ] Spelling/grammar
- [ ] Consistent formatting
```

## Documentation Links Structure

### From Project Root
```markdown
[Accessibility Guide](/docs/guides/ACCESSIBILITY_GUIDE.md)
[Phase 2 Status](/docs/phases/PHASE2_SESSION_COMPLETE.md)
[Performance Plan](/docs/phases/PHASE4_PERFORMANCE_PLAN.md)
```

### From README
```markdown
## Documentation
- [Accessibility Guide](./docs/guides/ACCESSIBILITY_GUIDE.md)
- [Phase Status](./docs/phases/STATUS_PHASES_1-3_COMPLETE.md)
- [Guides](./docs/guides/)
```

